Release V00-02-02

- Use log4cplus tool when available (for backward compatibility)
- Small fix in documentation

  -- Martin Wolf

- Make project compatible with Python 3

  -- Nathan Whitehorn


August 20, 2013 Meike de With (meike.de.with@desy.de)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Release V00-02-01

- Make project compatible with Python 3

  -- Nathan Whitehorn

- Added math documentation about the actual implementation of the 
  AvgDomDistQTotDom and EmptyHitsTrackLength cut variables of the 
  track_characteristics sub project

  -- Martin Wolf


February 21, 2013 Emanuel Jacobi  (emanuel.jacobi@desy.de)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Release V00-02-00

- Changed ZTravel calculation to take only the time of the first
  pulse per DOM
- Changed track_hits_separation_length calculation to take the time
  of the first pulse and the integrated charge of a DOM to determine
  the COG quartiles to not introduce data/MC discrepancies due to
  the NPulses issue.
- Call the Configure method of the I3ConditionalModule class,
  so the If module parameter does not get ignored.
- Make sure that CV does not cut on the given I3RecoPulseSeriesMaps
  based on the given Geometry.
- Improved documentation

  -- Martin Wolf

- Simplify the nPulses computation

  -- David Boersma

- Removed dependency on log4cplus

  -- Nathan Whitehorn

- Add svn keywords

  -- Emanuel Jacobi


September 26, 2012, Emanuel Jacobi  (emanuel.jacobi@desy.de)
